cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DL, cs.LG, cs.CV. 

The paper discusses a platform for ingesting and processing large amounts of scientific documents, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely sub-category, as it deals with the organization and retrieval of large amounts of textual data. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely, as it deals with NLP and ML techniques for processing natural language. cs.DL (Deep Learning) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible sub-categories, as they both deal with ML techniques. Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a less likely sub-category, but it is still possible as the paper mentions the challenges of processing bitmap images.
